Preheat your #oven{} to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Chop the @potatoes{450%grams} into 2cm chunks (no need to peel).

Halve and peel the @red onion{1}, then cut each half into 3 wedges.

Pop the potatoes and onion onto a large #baking tray{}. Drizzle with @olive oil{}, season with @salt{} and @pepper{}, then toss to coat. Spread out in a single layer.

> TIP: Use two baking trays if necessary.

When the oven is hot, roast on the top shelf until golden, ~{25-35%minutes}. Turn halfway through.

Meanwhile, slice your @ciabatta{1} widthways, into 6 slices.

Place your ciabatta slices onto a medium baking tray, drizzle with @olive oil{}, season with @salt{} and @pepper{} and toss to coat well.

When the potatoes have 10 mins left, bake on the middle shelf until golden, ~{8-10%minutes}.

While everything bakes, chop each @cooked beetroot{250%grams} into 2cm chunks.

> TIP: Wear gloves when handling the beetroot to avoid staining your hands.

== Beetroot and Walnut Potato Salad ==

In a large #bowl{}, add the @cider vinegar{15%ml}, @wholegrain mustard{17%grams}, @olive oil for the dressing{1%tbsp} and half the @honey{30%grams}.

> TIP: If your honey has hardened, put the sachet in a bowl of hot water for 1 min to loosen.

Season with @salt{} and @pepper{} and mix well.

== Assembly ==

Once your ciabatta toasts have finished cooking, remove from the oven and spread your @goat's cheese{75%grams} over the top of each slice.

Add your beetroot, roasted potatoes, onion and @baby leaf mix{50%grams} to your dressing and toss well to coat.

Share your salad between your bowls.

Top with your toasts and drizzle over the remaining honey.

Sprinkle over the @walnuts{20%grams} to finish.

Enjoy!